review_blob: Pours clean with a nice off-white head. Cloudy in appearance, but very palatable. Hop character is not overbearing, yet definitely pronounced. Overall a very delicious brew!

It tastes like an old Now and Later. Fucking gross. Very bitter, but not in a hoppy sense. It's almost expired or something. Just bad for start to finish. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

WOW! I was a born and raised MA fan of Pumpkinhead, but that has just changed! Amazing pumpkin pie-esque aroma, taste, AND finish! The spice note from soup to nuts is amazing! Granted, this is only one of the two seasonal's that I've had, but screw Shipyard! Lol

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Very aromatic beer! The mouth feel is nice and the finish is a little bitter. Nice off white head and initial butter flavor. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
beer_name: Green Flash / Founders Linchpin White India Pale Ale

review_blob:
A little on the bitter side, start and finish. Decent mouth feel, but that flavor profile is rough.

Very complex! Coffee aroma, yet citrus shines through as soon as its in your mouth. Finishes like a typical porter.

Very bitter initial palate. Doesn't finish very well either. Granted, it's an IPA, but still, quite "old world" compared to many others.

review_blob:
Very realistic! Sweet, yet a little tart. Brown sugar hints with the standard chocolate and mocha flavors. Easy finish; definitely something to write home about!

beer_name: Southern Tier Blackwater Series: Creme Brulee Stout

review_blob: Poured deep orange/amber color with a mid to small head. Fruity aroma mixed with malt-like overtone. Sweet finish that left a great taste.
Very light pour with quick fading head. Hints of malt and light spice. Semi-palatable worth a second glance... maybe bottle.
Very smooth and dark in color. Fruity undertone with creamy finish. Poured dark with a mid size head. Great all around brew!
Sweet for an IPA. Poured light amber with a medium cream head. Very palatable with a floral mid and finish. Definitely a brew worth going back to!

Like other raters claim, it does smell and taste like "Ludens" cough drops! Very uncharacteristic of any beer Ive tasted, thus far. Deep ruby pour with a pinkish medium head. Very sweet initial and finish with cherry following the whole way. Great Lambic!
Very conventional in taste and finish. Pours a light amber color with a fast receding small head. Smooth, yet flat bitter inital taste, with hop type light bitter finish.
Deep red in color with a creme color mid-size head. Piney aroma is stiff in the nose. Initial taste is very enjoyable with a creamy flavor of hops and carmelized sugar. Slow hop filled finish
Very noticeable malt flavors. Attractive color and head. Although it may be satisfying, it holds no lasting impressions.
Crisp, yet surprisingly smooth. Definite hints of chocolate throughout. A light finish with elements of honey. A very good amber for a higher gravity.

12oz bottle. This amber came highly recommended and I understand why. A very enjoyable ale! Off white head, golden tone. Sweet malty initial and mid taste. An almost fruit like finish. Very palletable!
This was a crowd favorite tonight. Personally, Ive had better, and I am in the infantile stages of rating! Deep earthy tones with a slight hop linger. I was expecting more.
I enjoy this beer from a sippers point. The hoppiness is almost too intense. The initial chocolate overtones are very attractive, but those become quickly overrun by the heavy hop linger.

I am kind of perplexed by the rating. Once again, I was spoiled with the other stouts I had before trying this one. Very dark, which is to be expected, but the linger is almost overwhelming. Maybe I need to read into this brand a bit more, but it didnt seem as high of a standard as is being rated on here.

If it wasnt for the glass I drank it in, I think Id score it differently... in other words, less. Super heavy hoppiness. Strong linger. Very palletable when served correctly. All in all, a standard imperial stout with a little character.

Although my peers may disagree, I really enjoyed this stout! The coffee acted as a reducer for the rest of the ingredients. Very subtle chocolate overtones and a very solid coffee linger. A slight hop bite, but nothing I wouldnt mind!
beer_name: Terrapin Wake-n-Bake Coffee Oatmeal Imperial Stout

review_blob: I was spoiled when I drank this. This was among the lower of the 6 imperial stouts I had tonight. Very heavy overtones. Lasting hop linger. I was anticipating more for such a highly rated brew.
beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: 12oz bottle. Very good stout. I am usually not one for milk types, but this has a characteristic that is distinguished. Hard chocolate tones with a coffee linger. Pours very well and has the looks of something youd take home to your parents!

12oz bottle. If I wanted a stereotypical cider, I wouldve gone to a gas station. This was a very standard cider and has no lasting impressions. Cheap aroma and less than average appearance. This fits right beside homemade fermented cider.

12oz bottle. Looks can be deceiving and this is proof! The bartender explained this as "a Corona with more flavor" and if his pallet is anything like his sex drive, Id feel horrible for his wife! A very "meh" kind of effect all around. If you were to slap an "Anheuser Busch" label on it, I wouldnt be surprised.

12oz bottle. For a traditional brewing method, it really lacks character. The initial reaction is tempting, but once at the end of the bottle, its something you wish had a little more style. Ive had some steam beers before and this is definitely the most bland of all.
12oz bottle. Not very appealing to my pallet. Strong overtones of hops. Bitter to an extent. Definitely something to settle for.
12oz bottle. Not what I expected from an IPA. Subtle honey undertones. Hoppy after affect. Slight linger. All in all, a surprising beer from the the north east!
12oz bottle. Very typical Pale Ale. A hint of metallic smell. Lingers quite a bit.
